Preconditions:
- The method takes three integer parameters: x, y, and z.
- The values of x, y, and z are between 1 and 50 (inclusive).

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the maximum possible length of the new string.
- The new string is formed by concatenating some (possibly all or none) of the strings "AA", "BB", and "AB" in some order.
- The new string does not contain the substring "AAA" or "BBB".